!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

discussion /dɪˈskʌʃən/

(discussions) 

1. N-VAR If there is discussion about something, people talk about it, often in order to reach a decision. 讨论 

例： There was a lot of discussion about the wording of the report. 有很多关于该份报告措词的讨论。 

例： Board members are due to have informal discussions later on today. 董事会成员们预定在今天稍后进行非正式讨论。 

2. PHRASE If something is under discussion , it is still being talked about and a final decision has not yet been reached. 在讨论中 

3. N-COUNT A discussion of a subject is a piece of writing or a lecture in which someone talks about it in detail. 详述 

例： For a discussion of biology and sexual politics, see chapter 

4. 欲获得一个生物学与性别政治学的论述，请看第4章。 

4. ADJ A discussion document or paper is one that contains information and usually proposals for people to discuss. 供讨论的 [ADJ n] 

例： ...a NASA discussion paper on long-duration ballooning. …一份美国国家航空航天局关于长时间气球飞行的讨论文件。

</div>

